                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18301209-258-victim2163 t18301209-258-viclabel1451"></join>. On the 12th of November a person came in and told me something; I went out, and saw the prisoner and another <rs id="t18301209-258-deflabel1452" type="occupation">boy</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18301209-258-defend2161 t18301209-258-deflabel1452"></join> running on the opposite side - I followed them, and saw them join six others; they spoke a few words, and then ran on - I followed the prisoner; he threw a handkerchief out of his pocket - I took it up, and went and took the prisoner; this is the handkerchief - it is my master's.</p>
               <p>The prisoner put in a written Defence, stating that hearing an alarm he ran with others, but was innocent.</p>
               <p>Two witnesses gave the prisoner a good character.</p>
               <p>GUILTY. Aged 14.</p>
